<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id6c760dc5-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e" identifier="/us/usc/t33/s3003"><num value="3003">§ 3003.</num><heading> Authorized number on the active list</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id6c760dc6-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e" identifier="/us/usc/t33/s3003/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> Annual strength on active list</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The annual strength of the commissioned corps in officers on the lineal list of active duty officers of the corps shall be prescribed by law.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id6c760dc7-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e" identifier="/us/usc/t33/s3003/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Lineal list</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary shall maintain a list, known as the “lineal list”, of officers on active duty. Officers shall be carried on the lineal list by grade and, within grade, by seniority in grade.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id6c760dc8-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e">(<ref href="/us/pl/107/372/tII/s213">Pub. L. 107–372, title II, § 213</ref>, <date date="2002-12-19">Dec. 19, 2002</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/116/3083">116 Stat. 3083</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
